title: Running Out Of Money - Will Saudi Arabia Blink ? | www.ajc.com
text:
Protest in Qatif, Saudi Arabia Russia's unannounced air attacks in support of Syria's efforts in repelling rebels seeking to topple the regime of Syrian dictator Bashar-Al-Assad, caused considerable concern for coalition nations involved in the campaign to contain ISIS. For NATO and several key Middle Eastern nations directly threatened by ISIS, the rag tag group of loosely linked rebels, are not ISIS. Indeed most rebels are Sunni Muslims supported financially and therefore indirectly by noted Sunni Gulf States such as Saudi Arabia and the UAE. ...
